               <birth when="1884"> He was born at <placeName ref="LOC5597Sawa"/> in <date>1884</date>.</birth>
                  
                  
                  <floruit notBefore="1896" notAfter="1977">He was a prominent statesman and administrator, as well as an important figure in the history of Amharic literature. 
                     When he was 9 years old he moved to <placeName ref="LOC3786Harar"/> with his elder brother who became a secretary to 
                     <roleName type="title">rās</roleName> <persName ref="PRS6567Makwanne"/> where he was brought up as a family member. In <date>1896/97</date>, 
                     he was sent to <placeName ref="gn:2017370"/> where he joined St Petersburg military school and later Michael Artillery School. In <date>1908 </date> 
                     he returned to <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop"/>.  A year later, <date>1909</date>, he was sent to <placeName ref="gn:3017382"/> to study agriculture. 
                     On his return, he served the Imperial government for a long time in various posts. He was one of the intellectual reformist of the imperial government before the Italian war. 
                   He drafted the first Ethiopian Constitution which was promulgated in <date>1931</date>. Apart from his political and administrative activities,
                     his name is also closely linked to the emergence of Ethiopian drama and theatre.
                  </floruit>
               <death when="1977">He died at <placeName ref="LOC3875Hirna"/></death>
                  
                  
